choices.text:
Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have? Explain your answer
If we assume that each brother and sister has only one sibling, then the total number of siblings for all three brothers would be 6 (3 x 2). However, since it is mentioned that her brothers have two sisters, this means that Sally also has two sisters. Therefore, she has a total of four siblings: herself and her three brothers with their two sisters each.
